Special Topic:The Making and Remaking of Disneyland: Histories of the American Amusement Park.;Course Description:This course explores the life of Walt Disney and his park Disneyland. The course analyzes the influence of Disneyland and its culture in Southern California and beyond. Disneyland is considered within the context of the history of recreation and amusement parks, the importance of memory, and the interest in escapism. Topics of architecture and urban design, historical reenactment and re-creation, and artistic reinvention are central to the course.;Note: Zero Textbook Cost.
